messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Endpoint full path
- /profiles

Methods (based on the code)

- all HTTP methods acceptable: false
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation (how this was determined)
- index.js mounts the profile router at the prefix "/profiles" via: app.use('/profiles', profile).
- In routes/profile.js the relevant routes are:
  - router.post('/', createProfile) — this makes POST /profiles the route that invokes createProfile (so POST is true).
  - router.get('/', getProfilesByUser) — there is a GET handler on the same path (so GET is true).
  - router.get('/:id', getProfile), router.patch('/:id', updateProfile), router.delete('/:id', deleteProfile) are for /profiles/:id, not the root /profiles.
- There is no router.all, no explicit router.options or app.options handler for /profiles, and no explicit HEAD handler in the code. Therefore OPTIONS and HEAD are marked false (the decision follows only what is present in the source, per your instruction).
- TRACE, PUT and DELETE (on /profiles) have no handlers in the provided router for the /profiles path, so they are false.
